    <section class="card" id="teleop">
      <h2>Tele-Op</h2>

      <h3>Cycle time</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>We prioritize fast, repeatable cycles over risky peak scoring.</li>
        <li>We call out cycle status: “intake”, “transferring”, “scoring”, “reset”.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Drive coach communication</h3>
      <div class="callout">
        <strong>We work best with:</strong> a <strong>human player</strong> and active partner comms
        (simple, short callouts).
      </div>

      <ul>
        <li>We announce path changes early (e.g., “switching to left lane”).</li>
        <li>We confirm shared objectives (defense, lane control, endgame timing).</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- ENDGAME -->
    <section class="card" id="endgame">
      <h2>Endgame</h2>
      <p>
        We typically give drivers the last <strong>20 seconds</strong> to park and secure points.
      </p>

      <h3>Parking plan</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Full park:</strong> commit early if field traffic is high.</li>
        <li><strong>Partial park:</strong> if we’re finishing a final cycle, we switch at ~20s.</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="callout">
        <strong>Alliance cue:</strong> At <strong>0:25</strong> we call “endgame soon”; at <strong>0:20</strong> we commit.
      </div>
    </section>

